Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.04,0:00:02.68,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10\i1}Conan{\i0} is approaching its tenth anniversary!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.68,0:00:04.38,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10\q2}And once we make it through the first decade,\Nlet's aim for another one!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.38,0:00:07.94,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A costume party takes an unexpected\Ntwist and becomes a case!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.94,0:00:09.94,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This is the sad tale behind a clown!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.94,0:00:11.44,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.44,0:00:13.44,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and looks like a kid\Nbut has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.44,0:00:15.66,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.55,0:01:55.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you think?\NPretty cool, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.29,0:01:59.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I assume you're familiar with the Animeland theme park.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.55,0:02:02.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They asked me to be the director for a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.27,0:02:04.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There wasn't any point in doing it without a twist,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.35,0:02:05.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so I figured I'd give it a personal touch.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.77,0:02:09.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that surprise was a big hit.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.02,0:02:11.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I'll be the honorary director for a day next year again,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.49,0:02:13.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and every other year after.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.28,0:02:16.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll come and rent a costume off you, so make sure you stay in business!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.97,0:02:22.59,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I don't remember them saying anything like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.59,0:02:27.05,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Didn't he see how shocked everyone was at how weird he was being?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.01,0:02:39.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess this will do. I'll give it to you as a present, signed and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.89,0:02:43.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, there's no need...\NWait, were you dancing?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.52,0:02:46.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, there was\Nan earthquake at about 3pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.44,0:02:50.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was pretty strong, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.62,0:02:59.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're going to be directors for a day, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.74,0:03:02.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, we're going to a party,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.76,0:03:04.77,Signs,,0,0,0,,Minoru Kijima (30)\NMakeup Artist
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.69,0:03:04.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to celebrate these two getting married.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.75,0:03:07.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, a costume party?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.25,0:03:09.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's a bit embarrassing,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.27,0:03:10.65,Signs,,0,0,0,,Jiro Ishikawa (28)\NPhotographer
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.55,0:03:12.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\q2}but someone said a normal party would be boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.51,0:03:16.03,Signs,,0,0,0,,Yoko Nakamura (25)\NFashion Model
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.52,0:03:14.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And we couldn't really argue with her,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.59,0:03:16.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,since she's pretty influential.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.01,0:03:18.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A smile in your face,\Nand tears in your heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.22,0:03:22.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The makeup hides the tears,\Njust like with clowns.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.89,0:03:24.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oops, I forgot my hat.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.77,0:03:27.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What kind of costume\Nshould I wear next time?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.48,0:03:30.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This one? No, maybe this...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.69,0:03:33.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's Umeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.74,0:03:35.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one in charge of the party.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.95,0:03:38.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The earthquake shook me up,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.32,0:03:41.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but the preparations for the party are still underway.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.29,0:03:43.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No wonder, the editor-in-chief hates earthquakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.65,0:03:45.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She says this is the costume she's wearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.99,0:03:49.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, a clown?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.19,0:03:51.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. This is Umeda, our editor-in-chief.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.71,0:03:54.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Surprise! Don't I look great?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.30,0:03:56.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got an e-mail from Umeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.52,0:03:59.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She says she'll leave the door unlocked,\Nand we should come in as soon as we arrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.80,0:04:01.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.55,0:04:03.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's 4:30pm, so we'll get there\Nat 5pm sharp.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.65,0:04:12.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A party, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.69,0:04:13.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.57,0:04:18.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll go play pachinko and then get something tasty to eat, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.22,0:04:18.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.57,0:04:23.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could you look after this\Nfor us, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.32,0:04:24.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.79,0:04:27.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.13,0:04:36.42,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Get something tasty to eat, my foot.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.42,0:04:39.13,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}You splurged everything you had playing pachinko!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.13,0:04:41.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Some people are heartless.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.49,0:04:44.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's nothing wrong with picking up the balls somebody else dropped.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.14,0:04:46.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The world's turning more\Nand more miserable.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.79,0:04:48.64,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Who's more miserable, the world or you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.15,0:05:02.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, an e-mail with a photo of a woman dressed up as a clown.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.91,0:05:06.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was on that girl's\Nmobile phone at 4:30pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.99,0:05:21.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cause of death is extreme pressure on the neck.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.22,0:05:22.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, strangulation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.15,0:05:26.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm certain of it, this is the woman we saw in that e-mail.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.75,0:05:31.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} saw an e-mail from the victim at 4:30pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.98,0:05:34.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The corpse was found at 5pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.39,0:05:36.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Taking all the information into account,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.95,0:05:40.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,we can say she was killed between 4:30pm and 5pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.79,0:05:43.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, what information?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.03,0:05:45.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan! Stop bothering\Npeople with questions!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.91,0:05:48.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, please don't mind him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.85,0:05:49.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, it's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.91,0:05:54.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When a person dies,\Ntheir muscles stiffen up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.33,0:05:57.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rigor mortis, right?\NI read about it in a book.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.34,0:06:01.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The body usually stiffens up about two hours after death.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.84,0:06:04.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if it's outside during a summer day,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.35,0:06:07.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,or in a warm place like here, where the heating's on,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.92,0:06:09.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it stiffens up faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.85,0:06:15.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But her body doesn't seem to have stiffened up yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.42,0:06:16.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Therefore, I can conclude
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.49,0:06:18.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that it hasn't been long since she died.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.86,0:06:25.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since it's 5:30 now, we can conclude she died just after 4:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.62,0:06:30.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And who was Umeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?\NDo you know anything about her?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.09,0:06:33.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was a talented editor-in-chief for a women's fashion magazine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.58,0:06:38.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kijima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who found the body,\Nis a famous makeup artist.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.75,0:06:41.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems the victim was the one who discovered him,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.49,0:06:43.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and helped him become who he is today.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.72,0:06:47.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Ishikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who was with her,\Nis a photographer for the same magazine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.55,0:06:51.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And there's also Yoko Nakamura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who worked as a model.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.19,0:06:59.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim's rings and necklaces are all missing from her jewelry box.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.94,0:07:04.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could the young man we saw earlier have stolen them?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.82,0:07:07.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You saw the killer?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.87,0:07:13.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When they reached this block of flats,\Nthese two saw a suspicious man running off.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.16,0:07:15.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was 5pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.20,0:07:19.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We saw him at the entrance, just after parking the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.65,0:07:23.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was wearing\Na black leather jacket.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.07,0:07:27.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A thief?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.34,0:07:28.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He looked like one.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.80,0:07:30.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or maybe he was a killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.72,0:07:32.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't say that, Kijima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.76,0:07:34.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was just joking.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.12,0:07:37.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Good evening, editor!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.87,0:07:39.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow, it's so warm.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.39,0:07:40.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It feels really nice, coming from the cold outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.76,0:07:43.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.48,0:07:45.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Footprints? No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.95,0:07:51.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Editor! There are\Nfootprints in the hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.94,0:07:53.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.41,0:07:56.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Editor?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.42,0:07:58.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Editor!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.32,0:08:01.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't move!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.21,0:08:05.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We mustn't tamper with the footprints. The phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.10,0:08:14.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn it! He cut the line.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.93,0:08:17.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't bring my mobile phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.61,0:08:18.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about the editor's?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.44,0:08:20.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know where it could be.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.48,0:08:25.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ishikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, let's split up and look for a public phone to call for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.03,0:08:28.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, we can't leave\NYoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} here alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.59,0:08:30.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kijima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, please stay here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.03,0:08:35.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Afterwards, they went off to search for a public phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.70,0:08:39.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was hard, but we eventually found one in front of the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.67,0:08:45.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They called 110 at 5:15.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.30,0:08:50.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We got here at 5:30, and saw that Umeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was already dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.22,0:08:53.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, how come neither of you were carrying a mobile phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.72,0:08:56.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She had hers before.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.32,0:08:59.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Don't bother people with questions!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.23,0:09:02.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Though to be honest, I was about to ask the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.69,0:09:05.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We left our mobile phones at the costume shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.69,0:09:11.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She hated mobile phones, since wherever she was, she'd get hounded by calls.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.74,0:09:16.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Particularly during parties, she would forbid anyone from bringing them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.74,0:09:19.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And she told me not to e-mail her.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.25,0:09:20.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.81,0:09:25.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Five years ago, you could find public phones anywhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.42,0:09:29.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but these days, they're a lot more scarce. What a strange time we live in.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.88,0:09:32.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know if we're\Nbetter off or worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.13,0:09:37.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Either way, whether the killer knew it or whether it was a mere coincidence,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.23,0:09:40.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the fact is somebody broke into this unlocked house.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.30,0:09:54.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Umeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was so focused on the preparations that she didn't notice the killer lying in wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.56,0:10:00.91,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}She was attacked from the back while she was laying down the cutlery here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.76,0:10:04.50,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If somebody came in through that hallway, she'd have noticed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.17,0:10:06.79,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And she'd have escaped.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.96,0:10:16.18,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But there are no signs of a struggle in this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.18,0:10:19.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, is this room identical\Nto how you found it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.52,0:10:20.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.59,0:10:23.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You remind me of a mystery series I watch on TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.10,0:10:26.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.11,0:10:28.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't me!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.03,0:10:30.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't do anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.78,0:10:32.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's him, it's him!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.11,0:10:35.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the man we saw running away from the block of flats.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.82,0:10:39.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I saw him in the park in front of the station looking pretty nervous,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.79,0:10:41.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so I decided to interrogate him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.32,0:10:42.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then he tried to escape,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.58,0:10:44.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so I caught him right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.60,0:10:47.11,Signs,,0,0,0,,Masataka Shimizu (25)\NPart-Time Worker
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.52,0:10:46.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know anything about this!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.08,0:10:49.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was carrying this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.59,0:10:53.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sato{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, can you show this to Kijima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and the others outside?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.92,0:10:54.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.59,0:10:57.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The footprints even match his shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.10,0:11:01.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I'm certain.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.23,0:11:04.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These were her favorite jewels.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.35,0:11:08.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you. Please wait here a little longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.36,0:11:10.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were asked to do it over the Internet?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.86,0:11:14.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I got a really interesting request.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.57,0:11:17.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The job consisted of\Ncoming here at 5pm,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.96,0:11:20.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,taking the jewelry on top of the table,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.65,0:11:22.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and taking it to the park in front of the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.62,0:11:26.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop making up stories!\NYou killed her for money, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.79,0:11:32.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No! When I got here, that clown was already dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.21,0:11:34.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I ran away because I didn't want to get in trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.93,0:11:39.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, this guy's pretty stubborn.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.14,0:11:41.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But isn't it strange
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.47,0:11:43.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that instead of running away from the crime scene,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.39,0:11:44.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he stayed around the park?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.64,0:11:48.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe somebody did hire him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.01,0:11:55.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Being a theme park's director for a day is exhausting...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.74,0:11:57.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm getting sleepy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.87,0:12:01.87,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Oh geez, he actually fell asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.90,0:12:11.41,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Beef stew?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.72,0:12:19.76,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's cold. The stove's been out for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.76,0:12:21.97,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But according to the stove knob, it should be on low flame...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.97,0:12:25.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective, please! You have to believe me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.07,0:12:26.18,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.18,0:12:28.52,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.52,0:12:29.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.52,0:12:31.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.36,0:12:35.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s going to get started soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.52,0:12:37.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.65,0:12:40.50,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He's not starting anything, he's sleeping for real.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.50,0:12:42.45,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}As usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.45,0:12:45.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, do you know what this is?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.43,0:12:48.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, this?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.36,0:12:51.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I asked the maintenance company in charge of this block of flats,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.05,0:12:53.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and they told me it's an earthquake detector for the gas.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.17,0:12:54.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An earthquake detector?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.84,0:12:56.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.36,0:12:59.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a device that cuts off the gas distribution when there's an earthquake.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.84,0:13:03.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Umeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} wanted one installed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.52,0:13:05.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It cuts off the gas when there's a strong earthquake.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.63,0:13:10.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It probably cut off from the 3pm earthquake, and she forgot to light up the stove again.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.35,0:13:13.14,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Did she forget to light up the stove again?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.14,0:13:15.86,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No... What if was she unable to?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.86,0:13:19.36,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}She was probably already dead by the time the earthquake hit at 3pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.36,0:13:23.62,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But the approximate time of death is between 4:30 and 5pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.59,0:13:29.23,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If she died before 3pm,\Nrigor mortis would've set in by 5:30,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.23,0:13:32.12,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}when Inspector Megure\Nand the others arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.12,0:13:34.81,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The heating was on,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.81,0:13:37.63,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}so rigor mortis\Nshould've set in even faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.63,0:13:40.43,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But that wasn't the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.43,0:13:42.07,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}So what {\i1}did{\i0} happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.07,0:13:44.07,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That would mean she was left somewhere cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.64,0:13:49.36,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's no way...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.36,0:13:51.64,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But there aren't many cold places in an ordinary house like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.44,0:13:57.94,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}To slow down rigor mortis...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.61,0:14:02.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you looking for?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.41,0:14:03.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you need any help finding it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.95,0:14:07.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, don't worry. I'll get it myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.45,0:14:15.83,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's not enough space under the bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.83,0:14:18.56,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And the closet wouldn't work, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.27,0:14:28.52,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Maybe here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.72,0:14:32.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, is there a ladder in this house?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.02,0:14:34.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A ladder? I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.54,0:14:36.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, there's one on the balcony.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.81,0:14:38.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I used it last week.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.65,0:14:40.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the balcony? Okay, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.41,0:14:47.32,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Grey makeup? It's fresh.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.04,0:14:53.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Brrr, it's cold!\NConan, where'd you go?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.72,0:15:04.51,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Artificial hair?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.51,0:15:06.74,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There was no need for a ladder...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.74,0:15:08.76,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I know who the killer is! {hannin wa ano hito! –Puto}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.56,0:15:22.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please wait, Detective!\NPlease believe me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.34,0:15:27.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right. You came here, but didn't kill the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.30,0:15:30.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who'd believe that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.03,0:15:32.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll hear the rest at HQ.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.70,0:15:34.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Detective Takagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.91,0:15:37.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, can we go too?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.56,0:15:41.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, right. By all means, feel free to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.25,0:15:43.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.61,0:15:46.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The costume party was a complete wreck.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.19,0:15:50.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And even worse, you lost an important person to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.32,0:15:53.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.27,0:15:57.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You fell asleep again?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.61,0:16:00.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, that was a rehearsal.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.50,0:16:05.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now witness, as Sleeping Kogoro solves the most complicated of cases.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.79,0:16:09.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kijima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, I'm sorry, but we can't allow you to leave yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.03,0:16:13.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.04,0:16:14.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ishikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.67,0:16:18.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,at what time did you meet Kijima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} today?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.00,0:16:20.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At 3pm, in front of\NBeika Department Store.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.75,0:16:25.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kijima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, before 3pm, where were you and what were you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.76,0:16:28.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A lot of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.74,0:16:31.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It sounds like you want to confirm my alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.47,0:16:35.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's indeed the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.05,0:16:40.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who you just took away, is not the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.02,0:16:44.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The man who killed Umeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is Kijima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who is right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.12,0:16:47.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you on about?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.49,0:16:51.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kijima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was with us the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.14,0:16:54.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He didn't have time to kill the editor.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.96,0:16:59.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only time he wasn't with us was when we went to look for a public phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.90,0:17:03.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the editor was already dead by then.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.05,0:17:09.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, Umeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was killed long before that...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.07,0:17:12.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Most likely, before you even met up with Kijima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.26,0:17:16.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the approximate time of death is between 4:30 and 5pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.72,0:17:21.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, didn't you see the e-mail from Umeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.54,0:17:27.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That only means that Umeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s mobile phone was used,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.63,0:17:30.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,not necessarily that she sent the e-mail herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.15,0:17:34.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, the rigor mortis hadn't set in yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.16,0:17:38.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Umeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s body wasn't in this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.10,0:17:42.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He hid it in a cold place before you arrived,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.67,0:17:45.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,in order to delay rigor mortis.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.54,0:17:47.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.52,0:17:50.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I saw her body at the same time as those two!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.42,0:17:53.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, what was that dead clown?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.22,0:17:55.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a doll.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.26,0:17:57.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A doll with clown makeup,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.14,0:17:58.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,with a similar stature to Umeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.72,0:18:04.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who suggested that today should be a costume party in the first place?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.83,0:18:06.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The editor.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.15,0:18:10.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ishikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, did she tell you that herself?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.65,0:18:15.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, Kijima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} told us the editor had suggested it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.92,0:18:18.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, Kijima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.37,0:18:23.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you know that this floor's gas setup has an earthquake detection device?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.67,0:18:25.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Earthquake?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.17,0:18:27.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You didn't know, did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.67,0:18:32.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Sato, can you bring the cooking pot here?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.14,0:18:33.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.89,0:18:40.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please tell us what's inside it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.61,0:18:44.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems she was making beef stew,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.39,0:18:46.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but it's not cooked yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.94,0:18:50.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If she'd left it as it was, I doubt it'd be ready on time for the party at 5pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.90,0:18:55.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Umeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was setting everything up so it was ready in time for the party.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.41,0:19:00.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As proof of that, the stove's flame had been set to low.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.16,0:19:03.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She intended to have it cooked on time for the party.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.72,0:19:07.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But because of the earthquake detector, the stove went out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.17,0:19:10.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Umeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} never turned the gas back on.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.67,0:19:13.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, she {\i1}couldn't{\i0} turn it back on.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.30,0:19:16.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why? Because she was already dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.14,0:19:18.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kijima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you killed her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.85,0:19:22.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You have no evidence!\NThis is ridiculous, I'm going home.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.85,0:19:27.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} is {\i1}not{\i0} done yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.11,0:19:33.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kijima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, before meeting up with Ishikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Yoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.11,0:19:39.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you came here and strangled Umeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\Nwho was setting everything up for the party.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.03,0:19:41.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Afterwards, you switched her body with a doll you'd set up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.00,0:19:46.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And why did you do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.34,0:19:51.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because you had to leave Umeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s body somewhere cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.55,0:19:54.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you wanted to have everyone believe
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.54,0:19:56.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that she was murdered shortly before the three of you arrived,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.72,0:20:00.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you couldn't leave the body in a room with the heating on.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.51,0:20:05.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kijima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you left without turning off the gas,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.67,0:20:07.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,because you wanted to ensure that the beef stew was ready
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.52,0:20:11.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,once you found Umeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s body hours later.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.39,0:20:13.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But unfortunately for you, there was an earthquake around 3pm...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.81,0:20:16.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the gas was stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.49,0:20:18.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not knowing that, you went shopping
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.27,0:20:21.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and went off to the costume shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.05,0:20:24.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And with Umeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s\Nphone that you'd stolen,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.81,0:20:27.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you sent that e-mail to make it look like she was alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.66,0:20:30.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And finally, you made sure everyone left their phones there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.23,0:20:35.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Upon finding the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.72,0:20:39.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you asked Ishikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to look for a public phone with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.63,0:20:46.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you knew Ishikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} would never leave his girlfriend alone with a corpse.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.68,0:20:50.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you'd be in this flat, under\Napparently normal circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.96,0:20:53.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Afterwards, you took\NUmeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s real body,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.94,0:20:56.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,which you'd hidden\Non the balcony,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.61,0:20:59.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and ditched the doll.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.32,0:21:07.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that moment, the gray clown makeup stained the balcony's curtains.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.07,0:21:10.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're lying!\NYou're making it all up!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.21,0:21:11.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You have no evidence!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.42,0:21:13.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.46,0:21:16.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please come out to the balcony.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.88,0:21:18.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.13,0:21:22.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kijima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, this is your car, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.50,0:21:37.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.40,0:21:39.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That woman deserved it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.94,0:21:42.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true that she made me who I am today,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.03,0:21:45.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but every time I found a girlfriend, she'd always step in the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.03,0:21:50.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She told me that if I ever broke up with her,\Nshe'd make sure I'd never find work!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.45,0:21:54.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was just like a clown,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.81,0:22:00.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,always hiding my true feelings under a veil of makeup!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.27,0:23:35.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fire chief for a day?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.73,0:23:38.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The old man never changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.05,0:23:42.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, is this going to...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.45,0:23:48.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I knew it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.06,0:23:58.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The transmitter's signal disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.22,0:24:04.22,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}They're going to assassinate someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.00,0:24:06.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The old man's in danger!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.18,0:24:09.52,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Just 90 metres...\NI have to make it in time!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.65,0:24:14.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haibara, do you know anything?\NWho's DJ?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.03,0:24:25.04,Signs,,0,0,0,,On the next Conan special:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.29,0:24:30.04,Signs,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.29,0:24:30.04,Signs,,0,0,0,,A transmitter and a bug
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.04,0:24:31.92,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Next time, it's the tenth anniversary...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.92,0:24:33.16,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,...special!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.16,0:24:35.05,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,At last, the Black Organization!
